<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,219,339]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1127,219,916]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="461" pageId="3" pageNumber="460">brown. Scapus light yellow. Pedicel dark brown. Genae light yellow or light brown (Fig. 2). Coryphe dark brown, with light yellow median line (Fig. 1). Pro- and mesonotum dark brown, with light yellow median carina. Fore wings dark brown, with light yellow transverse veins, each wing with two large light yellow areas – one basally and another one medially, near to costal margin (Fig. 2). Femora and fore and middle tibiae light brown, with dark brown spots. Hind tibiae light brown. Apices of spines on tibiae and tarsomeres black.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328688" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5328688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328688/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="460" startId="3.[113,152,1545,1564]" targetBox="[242,964,371,1526]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1088,1545,1592]" pageId="3" pageNumber="460">
Figs. 4–9. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov &amp; Mozaffarian, 2011" authorityName="Gnezdilov &amp; Mozaffarian" authorityYear="2011" box="[202,351,1546,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Eusarima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[202,351,1546,1564]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="460">Eusarima iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[355,421,1546,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="460" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(paratype). 4 – hind wing; 5 – aedeagus and phallobase, ventral view; 6 – aedeagus and phallobase, lateral view; 7 – style, lateral view; 8 – anal tube, dorsal view; 9 – anal tube, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,219,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[353,455,283,307]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,152,1545,1564]" captionTargetBox="[242,964,371,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-14@3.[229,974,363,1527]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 4–9. Eusarima iranica sp. nov. (paratype). 4 – hind wing; 5 – aedeagus and phallobase, ventral view; 6 – aedeagus and phallobase, lateral view; 7 – style, lateral view; 8 – anal tube, dorsal view; 9 – anal tube, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328688/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Figs. 5–9</figureCitation>
). Hind margin of pygofer almost straight. Anal tube long and narrow, rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[429,530,315,340]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,152,1545,1564]" captionTargetBox="[242,964,371,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-14@3.[229,974,363,1527]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 4–9. Eusarima iranica sp. nov. (paratype). 4 – hind wing; 5 – aedeagus and phallobase, ventral view; 6 – aedeagus and phallobase, lateral view; 7 – style, lateral view; 8 – anal tube, dorsal view; 9 – anal tube, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328688/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Figs. 8, 9</figureCitation>
). Anal column 0.3 times as long as anal tube. Phallobase slightly curved (in lateral view), with narrow supporting lobe below every ventral aedeagal hook (
<figureCitation box="[219,284,379,403]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,152,1545,1564]" captionTargetBox="[242,964,371,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-14@3.[229,974,363,1527]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 4–9. Eusarima iranica sp. nov. (paratype). 4 – hind wing; 5 – aedeagus and phallobase, ventral view; 6 – aedeagus and phallobase, lateral view; 7 – style, lateral view; 8 – anal tube, dorsal view; 9 – anal tube, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328688/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Each dorso-lateral phallobase lobe with narrow, acuminate subapical process. Ventral phallobase lobe long, wide, enlarged apically, with median concavity (
<figureCitation box="[992,1058,411,435]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,152,1545,1564]" captionTargetBox="[242,964,371,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-14@3.[229,974,363,1527]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 4–9. Eusarima iranica sp. nov. (paratype). 4 – hind wing; 5 – aedeagus and phallobase, ventral view; 6 – aedeagus and phallobase, lateral view; 7 – style, lateral view; 8 – anal tube, dorsal view; 9 – anal tube, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328688/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Apical aedeagal processes long, surpassing apical margin of phallobase. Ventral aedeagal hooks long, acuminate. Style with slightly convex hind margin, caudo-dorsal angle rounded (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,152,1545,1564]" captionTargetBox="[242,964,371,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-14@3.[229,974,363,1527]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 4–9. Eusarima iranica sp. nov. (paratype). 4 – hind wing; 5 – aedeagus and phallobase, ventral view; 6 – aedeagus and phallobase, lateral view; 7 – style, lateral view; 8 – anal tube, dorsal view; 9 – anal tube, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328688/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Сapitulum of style small, with neck, lateral and apical teeth well-developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,219,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Female genitalia. Hind margin of female sternum VII with large median semicircular process. Anal tube elongate, narrow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,219,916]" box="[181,782,603,627]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Total length. Males: 4.7–5.0 mm. Females: 5.1–5.3 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="461" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,219,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,396,635,659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species differs from closely related 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[811,947,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Eusarima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleriana">
<emphasis box="[811,947,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">E. helleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the coloration of the metope, the shape of the costal margin and the coloration of fore wings, and the absence of processes on ventral aedeagal hooks (see also the key below). In the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="DLABOLA (1997)" authorityName="DLABOLA" authorityYear="1997" box="[183,509,732,756]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Eusarima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleriana">
<emphasis box="[183,325,733,756]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">E. helleriana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DLABOLA J." box="[334,509,732,756]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" pagination="301 - 319" refId="ref2389" refString="DLABOLA J. 1997: Mycterodus verwandte Taxone und sieben neue Zikadenarten (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 44 (1995): 301 - 319." type="journal article" year="1997">DLABOLA (1997)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
mentioned that the fore wing of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DLABOLA" authorityYear="1997" box="[878,1020,733,756]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Eusarima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleriana">
<emphasis box="[878,1020,733,756]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">E. helleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has large light and dark maculae in its proximal half (‘grössere helle und dunkle Makel besonders in der Basalhälfte der Vorderflügel’) (
<bibRefCitation author="DLABOLA J." box="[532,694,796,820]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" pagination="301 - 319" refId="ref2389" refString="DLABOLA J. 1997: Mycterodus verwandte Taxone und sieben neue Zikadenarten (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 44 (1995): 301 - 319." type="journal article" year="1997">DLABOLA 1997</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 11). 
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov &amp; Mozaffarian, 2011" authorityName="Gnezdilov &amp; Mozaffarian" authorityYear="2011" box="[808,997,797,820]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Eusarima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[808,997,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Eusarima iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1006,1093,796,819]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DLABOLA" authorityYear="1997" box="[268,406,829,852]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Eusarima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleriana">
<emphasis box="[268,406,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">E. helleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is characterized by the presence of two large light yellow areas (not maculae!) basally and medially on fore wings (Fig. 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,779,891,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,219,916]" box="[151,779,891,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,892,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="461">Etymology.</emphasis>
